Homomorphic encryption also synergizes powerfully with zero-knowledge proofs (ZK proofs).

Zero-knowledge systems allow one party to prove that a computation was performed correctly without revealing the underlying inputs.

Combining HE with ZK creates verifiable encrypted computation.

For example:

HE keeps the medical data encrypted.

ZK proofs verify that the AI analysis was performed honestly.


This prevents malicious cloud providers from faking diagnostic outputs or manipulating encrypted computations.

